    "updated_at": "2016-03-22T19:33:28Z",
    "body": ":+1: On the deprecations. I was actually just bitten by `char_at` because I did not properly understood how it worked. My assumption was that the position you provide was for the position of the character, while actually of course it's the position of the byte you're trying to use as the first byte of a character. To me this was counterintuitive.\n\nI think we should encourage using `char_indexes` as much as possible, that provides an actually safe api. If you know what you're doing the slicing approach seems fine.\n",
